SENEGAL forward Sadio Mane believes their experience will be an advantage when they face Egypt in the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations final this evening at the Olembe Stadium Cameroon. Mane and his teammates are seeking to win the title for the first time since Senegal made its debut appearance in 1965. Mane scored his third goal of the tournament in the Indomitable Lions’ 3-1 semi-final defeat of Burkina Faso on Wednesday and Liverpool forward is confident that they have what it takes to lift the trophy.   Lampard begins Everton reign with Brentford win     Falconets trash Cameroon to edge closer to World Cup berth     Egypt players promised hefty rewards to win AFCON title   “Experience is a good asset. I think that has always been the case since the start of this tournament. We suffered so much with a lot of Covid cases and several injuries too. “We had a very difficult time but with our experience, we kept calm until we recovered the whole group. - Advertisement - “We played a final last time, so we have experience and we will try to win this trophy.”